        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add bulk skill rescan admin tool",
        "body": "## Why\n\nClawHub had a one-skill ClawScan rescan command, but no operator-safe way to refresh the latest version of every active skill without queueing the whole corpus at once. This adds a paced admin flow that batches work, waits for each batch to drain, and leaves existing higher-priority scan jobs alone.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Adds a low-priority `bulk-rescan` security scan source and admin-only Convex internals for enqueueing latest active skills in bounded batches.\n- Exposes admin API endpoints at `POST /api/v1/skills/-/rescan-batch` and `POST /api/v1/skills/-/rescan-batch/status`.\n- Adds `clawhub-mod skills rescan-all` with dry-run, cursor resume, max-skill cap, JSON events, human-readable progress, polling, and fail-fast support.\n- Includes coverage for legacy active skills with missing `moderationStatus`, existing active job preservation, status aggregation, and the mod CLI pacing loop.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `bun run test -- convex/securityScan.test.ts convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts packages/clawhub-mod/src/commands/moderation.test.ts`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --reviewer codex --fallback-reviewer none`\n",
